"{\"uid\": \"fansided.com-posts-2024-olympic-gymnastics-dates-teams-schedule\", \"text\": \"The2024 Paris Olympic Gamesare upon us. With\\u00c2206 countries\\u00c2\\u00a0partaking in the transnational affair, excitement is brewing around the planet.\\u00c2  One of the most captivating aspects of theOlympicsis the\\u00c2extensive list\\u00c2\\u00a0of sports and competitions, making it easy to find something for everyone. North of 10,000 athletes are battling across\\u00c2329 medal events, ensuring all fans are actively engaged in the Paris Games. Among the most popular of the bunch is gymnastics.  Per an\\u00c2analytical breakdown\\u00c2\\u00a0from the International Olympic Committee (IOC), gymnastics is in the top echelon of well-received sports at the global outing.  With that in mind, when will the gymnastics contests at the 2024 Paris Summer Games begin? Moreover, which nations will be participating, and who will represent them?  Below, we have outlined everything you need to know regarding gymnastics scheduling, who's going for gold and more at this year's rendition of the Olympics.  Gymnastics at the Paris Olympics spans\\u00c2\\u00a010\\u00c2\\u00a0days from July 27th to August 5th.  We know France is the host nation for the Olympics, specifically Paris. But where in the capital city of the country will the gymnastics events specifically happen?  Bercy Arena will be where anything gymnastics-related takes place for the Summer Games.  12\\u00c2\\u00a0countries will duke it out between the team men's and women's formats, nominating four of their five squad members for a respective event.\\u00c2  The dozen groups in the ladies' collaborative contests are:\\u00c2  Meanwhile, the gentleman will still feature the USA, Japan, China, Italy, Canada, Germany and Great Britain. But the following nations will take the place of the other five nations from the female side:  At the Paris Summer Games, there are 14 combined gymnastics competitions for men (eight) and women (six). Below, you can see the various events and when they will happen.  Date  Event(s)  Time (ET)  July 27  Men's Qualification (3 Subdivisions)  Subdivision 1: 5 a.m.Subdivision 2: 9:30 a.m.Subdivision 3:2 p.m.  July 28  Women's Qualification (5 Subdivisions)  Subdivision 1:3:30 a.m.Subdivision 2:5:40 a.m.Subdivision 3:8:50 a.m.Subdivision 4:12 p.m.Subdivsion 5:3:10 p.m.  July 29  Men's Team Final  11:30 a.m.  July 30  Women's Team Final  12:15 p.m.  July 31  Men's All-Around Final  11:30 a.m.  August 1  Women's All-Around Final  12:15 p.m.  August 3  Women's Vault FinalMen's Pommel Horse Final  10:20 a.m.11:16 a.m.  August 4  Men's Rings FinalWomen's Uneven Bars FinalMens Vault Final  9 a.m.9:40 a.m.10:24 a.m.  August 5  Men's Parallel Bars FinalWomen's Balance Beam FinalMen's Horizontal Bar FinalWomen's Floor Exercise Final  5:45 a.m.6:38 a.m.7:33 a.m.8:23 a.m.  You can watch the 2024 Olympic gymnastics live via NBC, E!, Telemundo and Universo. Alternatively, you can stream the competitions on Peacock, NBCOlympics.com, NBC.com, or the NBC/NBC Olympics apps.  Russia, the reigning men's and women's team all-around Gold medalists at the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, is barred from the 2024 Games. The country's invasion of Ukraine largely contributed to the decision to exclude them from the events in Paris.  \\u00c2\\u00a9 2026Minute Media-All Rights Reserved. The content on this site is for entertainment and educational purposes only. Betting and gambling content is intended for individuals 21+ and is based on individual commentators' opinions and not that of Minute Media or its affiliates and related brands. All picks and predictions are suggestions only and not a guarantee of success or profit. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, crisis counseling and referral services can be accessed by calling 1-800-GAMBLER.\"}"